Sentencas: In part I of the present study, a two-dimensional isothermal mechanistic model of a composite yttria/scandia stabilized zirconia anode-supported multiple layers solid oxide fuel cell (Ni-YSZ vertical bar Ni-ScSZ vertical bar ScSZ vertical bar LSM-ScSZ) was developed, calibrated and validated using a button cell setup.
Titulo: Modeling of an anode-supported Ni-YSZ|Ni-ScSZ|ScSZ| LSM-ScSZ multiple layers SOFC cell -: Part II.: Simulations and discussion

Sentencas: In this paper, the model was further validated for extended operating conditions of fuel and oxidant compositions, which confirmed the robustness of the model.
Titulo: Modeling of an anode-supported Ni-YSZ|Ni-ScSZ|ScSZ| LSM-ScSZ multiple layers SOFC cell -: Part II.: Simulations and discussion

Sentencas: Since an important attribute of this model is its ability to accurately describe the effect of cell microstructure on cell performance, a large section of part II is devoted to sensitivity analysis of various microstructure parameters (cathode area, porosity, layer thickness and particle radius) on cell performance.
Titulo: Modeling of an anode-supported Ni-YSZ|Ni-ScSZ|ScSZ| LSM-ScSZ multiple layers SOFC cell -: Part II.: Simulations and discussion

Sentencas: In particular, the simulation results have shown how the button cell microstructure should be modified to optimize its performance.
Titulo: Modeling of an anode-supported Ni-YSZ|Ni-ScSZ|ScSZ| LSM-ScSZ multiple layers SOFC cell -: Part II.: Simulations and discussion

Sentencas: The proposed model could be used as a bridge between micro-scale electrode models and macro-scale unit cell simulation, thus being a useful tool for electrode design.
Titulo: Modeling of an anode-supported Ni-YSZ|Ni-ScSZ|ScSZ| LSM-ScSZ multiple layers SOFC cell -: Part II.: Simulations and discussion
